Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

> For crispier carrots, place a foil-lined baking sheet inside the oven as it preheats.

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @carrots{4}(peeled and cut on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick
pieces). Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Thinly slice @chives{¼%ounce}.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Boil
until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ¼ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and
return potatoes to pot.

Meanwhile, toss carrots on a foil-lined #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @Fry Seasoning{1%tsp},
and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast, tossing halfway through, until lightly
browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Use 2 tsp Fry Seasoning for 4 servings.

On a #plate{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup}, remaining Fry Seasoning, and a big
pinch of salt and pepper. Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season
all over with salt and pepper. Brush chicken all over with half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon}.
Working one piece at a time, coat chicken on both sides with panko mixture, pressing to
adhere.

Heat a ¼-inch-layer of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to the pan, add chicken and
cook until panko is golden brown and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.
Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

To pot with potatoes, add remaining sour cream, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and half the chives.
Mash with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed,
until smooth.

Divide chicken, carrots, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle chicken with @hot honey{¾%ounce}
(or serve it on the side for dipping). Sprinkle potatoes with remaining chives.